The President of the United States, Barack Obama, spoke to the President of China, Xi Jinping, on March 9th about the situation in Ukraine. They both agreed that it was important to focus on common interests and work together to address regional and global challenges. They also agreed that it was important to reduce tensions and find a peaceful resolution to the dispute between Russia and Ukraine. They emphasized the importance of upholding principles of sovereignty and territorial integrity, both in Ukraine and in the broader international system. President Obama expressed his goal of restoring Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity and allowing the Ukrainian people to determine their own future without interference from other countries. They agreed to continue to stay in touch as events unfold.